# Presence of this file enables SSH agent forwarding for the project.
# Content is ignored — sbx only checks that the file exists.
#
# When enabled, sbx mounts:
#   - $SSH_AUTH_SOCK   (so `ssh`/`git` inside the container can sign keys)
#   - ~/.ssh/config       (read-only)
#   - ~/.ssh/known_hosts  (read-only)
#
# Toggle with: sbx config ssh on  /  sbx config ssh off
